03/08/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The country celebrated its national holiday Sunday (August 2nd), marking the 106th anniversary of the Ilinden Uprising and the 65th anniversary of the first Anti-Fascist Assembly for People's Liberation of Macedonia.
In Krusevo, where the main celebrations were held, President Gjorge Ivanov said good relationships among the various religious groups -- and with neighbours -- are crucial to Macedonia's future.
(A1, Makfax, MIA, MRT, Sitel - 02/08/09)
